Icon manager
===============================================================================
Add/remove icons from top bar panel by simple editing gsettings

How to use?
===============================================================================
1. run dconf-editor
Press Alt+F2, type dconf-editor

2. Find settings
/org/gnome/shell/extensions/icon-manager

3. Edit key
 * top-bar: put icons that you want to remove from top-bar or move from tray bar
 * desaturation-factor: 0 -- no desaturation, 1 -- full desaturation (grayscale)
   or any number between
 
4. To accept changes you need to restart gnome-shell
Alt+F2, type r
